parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear-view camera can increase the risk of accidents or injuries while reversing, especially in low-visibility conditions, as the driver may not be able to see obstacles or pedestrians behind the vehicle.
symptoms: The rear-view camera displays distorted images
making it difficult or impossible for the driver to see obstacles or pedestrians while reversing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure and seizure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents, strandings, or injuries, particularly on busy roads or highways.
symptoms: heavy and foul-smelling smoke comes out of the tailpipe
the engine makes loud knocking noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut off unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: the vehicle cannot be put into neutral
and warnings appear on the phone app regarding various systems such as anti-lock brake

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty battery or electrical drain can cause the vehicle to experience battery drain, leading to unexpected shutdowns and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: and warnings appear on the phone app regarding various systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the camera system can cause a loss of visibility while parking or reversing, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The backup camera and 360-degree camera display a blue image
the backup camera does not work until the vehicle is restarted
and the camera malfunction occurs while parallel parking or in a parking garage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The powertrain malfunctioning can cause the vehicle to lose acceleration, resulting in accidents or near-misses, especially when merging into traffic or cruising on the highway.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly shifts into a lower gear
and slowing down to an unacceptable speed; the accelerator pedal becomes unresponsive
causing the vehicle to stall or lose power; the vehicle experiences sudden loss of power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The driveshaft vibration can cause loss of control, accidents, or damage to other vehicle components, leading to safety risks and costly repairs.
symptoms: The vehicle exhibits strong vibrations at certain speeds
even after replacing the driveshaft multiple times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose acceleration, resulting in accidents or near-misses, especially when merging into traffic or cruising on the highway.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly shifts into a lower gear
and slowing down to an unacceptable speed; the accelerator pedal becomes unresponsive
causing the vehicle to stall or lose power.
